dent of its size i.e. buildings, bridges, roads, dams, pavements, pipes, drains etc. It is composed of natural aggregates
of diï¬erent granulometries (gravel, ï¬ne gravel, sand) bonded together by hydrated cement paste. Chemical admix-
tures may also be added to enhance speciï¬c properties of the fresh or hardened concrete, such as workability,
durability, or early and ï¬nal strength. Concrete is workable right after production so that it can be transported,
poured, pumped, installed, compacted on the project site and over time it hardens and develops strengths. It is
delivered to the construction site via concrete mixer trucks that usually have 8 m3 load.
